httpserver

  • Classes in httpserver used by httpserver 
    Class and Description
    HTTPException
    An HTTPException is just a generic exception.
    HTTPHandler
    An HTTPHandler is what all handlers used by your server descend from.
    HTTPRequest
    An HTTPRequest takes an incoming connection and parses out all of the relevant data, supposing the connection follows HTTP protocol.
    HTTPResponse
    An HTTPResponse is used to set output values, and to write those values to the client.
    HTTPRouter
    An HTTPRouter is used to route incoming requests to specific handlers.
